[normal]  [bold]Introduction[bold]How do [bold]Government and local authorities identify demand for passenger transport in isolated communities (including rural and urban areas and island communities)?[bold]What are the main challenges associated with providing[bold] and funding[bold] better and more consistent bus and rail services to isolated communities? How can these challenges be overcome?[bold] How can these services be made more affordable?[bold]To what extent are the needs of different groups of passengers (e.g. people with disabilities, older people and younger people) taken into account in determining the provis[bold]ion of public transport to isolated communities?[bold]Multimodal access to stations
